### Content Calendar API Tests
### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080

### 1. Test Home Endpoint
GET {{baseUrl}}/
Accept: application/json

### 2. Get All Content
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/content
Accept: application/json

### 3. Create New Content
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/content
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Test Article",
  "desc": "This is a test article description",
  "status": "IDEA",
  "contentType": "ARTICLE",
  "dateCreated": "2025-09-15T20:00:00",
  "dateUpdated": null,
  "url": "https://example.com/test"
}

### 4. Get Content by ID (use ID from previous response)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/content/1
Accept: application/json

### 5. Update Content
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/content/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Updated Test Article",
  "desc": "This is an updated test article description",
  "status": "IN_PROGRESS",
  "contentType": "ARTICLE",
  "dateCreated": "2025-09-15T20:00:00",
  "dateUpdated": "2025-09-15T21:00:00",
  "url": "https://example.com/updated-test"
}

### 6. Search by Title
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/content/filter/Updated
Accept: application/json

### 7. Search by Status
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/content/filter/status/IN_PROGRESS
Accept: application/json

### 8. Test Error Cases - Get Non-existent Content
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/content/999
Accept: application/json

### 9. Test Error Cases - Update Non-existent Content
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/content/999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Should Fail",
  "desc": "This should return 404",
  "status": "IDEA",
  "contentType": "ARTICLE",
  "dateCreated": "2025-09-15T20:00:00",
  "url": "https://example.com/fail"
}

### 10. Test Error Cases - Delete Non-existent Content
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/content/999

### 11. Create Content with Validation Errors (missing required fields)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/content
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "desc": "Missing title - should fail validation",
  "status": "IDEA",
  "contentType": "ARTICLE"
}

### 12. Delete Content (use existing ID)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/content/1

### 13. Verify Deletion
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/content/1
Accept: application/json
